SIMPLE: civilization
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Civilization
<hw>Civ`i*li*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>civilisation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of civilizing,
or the state of being civilized; national culture; refinement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our manners, our civilization, and all the good things connected
with manners, and with <qex>civilization</qex>, have, in this European
world of ours, depended for ages upon two principles -- . . . the spirit
of a gentleman, and spirit of religion.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Rendering a criminal process
civil.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Civilize</ent>⟦br⟧
